#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:64
msgid ""
"UTF-16 (16-bit Unicode Transformation "
"Format)是UCS-2的拓展，用一个或者两个16位的码元来表示码位，可以对0到0x10FFFF的码位进行编码。"
msgstr ""
"UTF-16 (16-bit Unicode Transformation Format) is an extension of UCS-2. "
"It uses one or two 16-bit code units to represent a code point and can encode "
"code points from 0 to 0x10FFFF."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:67
msgid "等价性问题"
msgstr "Equivalence Issues"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:70
msgid "简介"
msgstr "Introduction"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:71
msgid ""
"Unicode（统一码）包含了许多特殊字符，为了使得许多现存的标准能够兼容，提出了Unicode等价性（Unicode "
"equivalence）。在字符中，有些在功能上会和其它字符或字符序列等价。因此，Unicode将一些码位序列定义成相等的。"
msgstr ""
"Unicode contains many special characters. Unicode equivalence was introduced "
"to keep many existing standards compatible. Some characters are functionally "
"equivalent to other characters or character sequences, so Unicode defines "
"some code point sequences as equal."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:73
msgid ""
"Unicode提供了两种等价概念：标准等价和兼容等价。前者是后者的一个子集。例如，字符n后接着组合字符 `~` "
"会（标准和兼容）等价于Unicode字符ñ。而合字ﬀ则只有兼容等价于两个f字符。"
msgstr ""
"Unicode provides two equivalence concepts: canonical equivalence and "
"compatibility equivalence. The former is a subset of the latter. For example, "
"the character n followed by the combining character `~` is canonically and "
"compatibly equivalent to the Unicode character ñ. The ligature ﬀ is only "
"compatibly equivalent to two f characters."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:75
msgid "Unicode正规化是文字正规化的一种形式，是指将彼此等价的序列转成同一列序。此序列在Unicode标准中称作正规形式。"
msgstr ""
"Unicode normalization is a form of text normalization. It converts sequences "
"that are equivalent to each other into the same sequence. This sequence is "
"called a normalization form in the Unicode standard."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:77
msgid "对于每种等价概念，Unicode又定义两种形式，一种是完全合成的，一种是完全分解的。因此，最后会有四种形式，其缩写分别为：NFC、NFD、NFKC、NFKD。对于Unicode的文字处理程序而言，正规化是很重要的。因为它影响了比较、搜索和排序的意义。"
msgstr ""
"For each equivalence concept, Unicode defines two forms: one fully composed "
"and one fully decomposed. This gives four forms in total, abbreviated as NFC, "
"NFD, NFKC, and NFKD. Normalization is important for Unicode text processing "
"because it affects the meaning of comparison, search, and sorting."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:80
msgid "标准等价"
msgstr "Canonical Equivalence"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:81
msgid ""
"统一码中标准等价的基础概念为字符的组成和分解的交互使用。合成指的是将简单的字符合并成较少的预组字符的过程，如字符n和组合字符 `~` "
"可以组成统一码ñ。分解则是反向过程，即将预组字符变回部件。"
msgstr ""
"The basic concept behind canonical equivalence in Unicode is the interplay "
"between character composition and decomposition. Composition merges simple "
"characters into fewer precomposed characters. For example, the character n "
"and the combining character `~` can form the Unicode character ñ. "
"Decomposition is the reverse process, turning precomposed characters back "
"into their components."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:83
msgid ""
"标准等价是指保持视觉上和功能上的等价。例如，含附加符号字母被视为和分解后的字母及其附加符号是标准等价。换句话说，预组字符‘ü’和由‘u’及 "
"‘¨’所组成的序列是标准等价。相似地，统一码统合了一些希腊附加符号和外观与附加符号类似的标点符号。"
msgstr ""
"Canonical equivalence preserves visual and functional equivalence. For "
"example, a letter with a diacritic is considered canonically equivalent to "
"the decomposed letter plus its diacritic. In other words, the precomposed "
"character ‘ü’ is canonically equivalent to the sequence made of ‘u’ and ‘¨’. "
"Similarly, Unicode unifies some Greek diacritics with punctuation marks that "
"look like diacritics."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:86
msgid "兼容等价"
msgstr "Compatibility Equivalence"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:87
msgid "兼容等价的范围较标准等价来得广。如果序列是标准等价的话就会是兼容等价，反之则未必对。兼容等价更关注在于纯文字的等价，并把一些语义上的不同形式归结在一起。"
msgstr ""
"Compatibility equivalence is broader than canonical equivalence. If a "
"sequence is canonically equivalent, it is also compatibly equivalent, but the "
"reverse is not necessarily true. Compatibility equivalence focuses more on "
"plain-text equivalence and groups together some forms that differ "
"semantically."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:89
msgid "例如，上标数字和其所使用的数字是兼容等价，但非标准等价。其理由为下标和上标形式虽然在某些时侯属于不同意义，但若应用程序将他们视为一样也是合理的（虽然视觉上可区分）。如此，在统一码富文件中，上标和下标就可以以比较不累赘地方式出现（见下一节）。"
msgstr ""
"For example, superscript digits and the digits they use are compatibly "
"equivalent, but not canonically equivalent. Although subscript and "
"superscript forms may have different meanings in some cases, it can also be "
"reasonable for an application to treat them as the same, even though they are "
"visually distinguishable. This allows superscripts and subscripts to appear "
"less awkwardly in rich Unicode text."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:91
msgid "全角和半角的片假名也是一种兼容等价但不是标准等价。如同合字和其部件序列。其只有视觉上但没有语义上的区别。换句话说，作者通常没有特别宣称使用合字是一种意思，而不使用是另一种意思。相对地，这尽限于印刷上的选择。"
msgstr ""
"Full-width and half-width katakana are also compatibly equivalent but not "
"canonically equivalent, as are ligatures and their component sequences. These "
"forms differ visually but not semantically. In other words, authors usually "
"do not explicitly state that using a ligature has one meaning while not using "
"it has another; it is only a typographic choice."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:93
msgid "文字处理软件在实现统一码字符串的搜索和排序时，须考虑到等价性的存在。如果没有此特性的话，用户在搜索时将无法找到在视觉上无法区分的字形。"
msgstr ""
"Text-processing software must account for equivalence when implementing "
"search and sorting for Unicode strings. Without this feature, users may fail "
"to find glyphs that are visually indistinguishable."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:95
msgid ""
"统一码提供了一个标准的正规化算法，可将所有相同的序列产生一个唯一的序列。 其等价准绳可以为标准的（NF）或兼容的（NFK）。 "
"既然可以任意选择等价类中的元素，对每一个等价标准有多个标准形式也是有可能的。 "
"统一码为每一种等价准绳分别提供两种正规形式：合成用的NFC和NFKC以及分解用的NFD和NFKD。 "
"而不论是组合的或分解的形式，都会使用标准顺序，以此限制正规形式只有唯一形式。"
msgstr ""
"Unicode provides a standard normalization algorithm that can produce a unique "
"sequence for all equivalent sequences. Its equivalence criterion can be "
"canonical (NF) or compatible (NFK). Because any element in an equivalence "
"class can be chosen, multiple standard forms are possible for each "
"equivalence criterion. Unicode provides two normalization forms for each "
"criterion: NFC and NFKC for composition, and NFD and NFKD for decomposition. "
"Both composed and decomposed forms use canonical ordering, which constrains "
"the normalization form to a single unique form."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:98
msgid "正规化"
msgstr "Normalization"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:99
msgid ""
"为了比较或搜索统一码字符串，软件可以使用合成或分解形式其中之一。 只要被比较或搜索的字符串使用的形式是相同的，哪种选择都没关系。 "
"另一方面，等价概念的选择则会影响到搜索结果。 "
"譬如，有些合字如ﬃ（U+FB03）、罗马数字如Ⅸ（U+2168），甚至是上标数字如⁵（U+2075）有其个别统一码码位。 "
"标准正规形式并不会影响这些结果。 但兼容正规形式会分解ﬃ成f、f、i。所以搜索U+0066（f）时，在NFKC中会成功，但在NFC则会失败。 "
"同样地有在预组罗马数字Ⅸ 中搜索拉丁字母I（U+0049）。类似地，“⁵”会转成“5”。"
msgstr ""
"To compare or search Unicode strings, software can use either composed or "
"decomposed form. The choice does not matter as long as the strings being "
"compared or searched use the same form. However, the choice of equivalence "
"concept affects search results. For example, some ligatures such as ﬃ "
"(U+FB03), Roman numerals such as Ⅸ (U+2168), and even superscript digits such "
"as ⁵ (U+2075) have their own Unicode code points. Canonical normalization "
"does not affect these results, but compatibility normalization decomposes ﬃ "
"into f, f, and i. Therefore, a search for U+0066 (f) succeeds in NFKC but "
"fails in NFC. The same applies when searching for the Latin letter I "
"(U+0049) inside the precomposed Roman numeral Ⅸ. Similarly, “⁵” is converted "
"to “5”."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:101
msgid ""
"对于浏览器，将上标转换成到基下划线未必是好的，因为上标的信息会因而消失。为了允许这种不同，统一码字符数据库句含了兼容格式标签，其提供了兼容转换的细节。在合字的情况下，这个标签只是"
" ``<compat>`` ，而在上标的情况下则为 ``<super>`` "
"。丰富文件格式如超文本置标语言则会使用兼容标签。例如，HTML使用自定义标签来将“5”放到上标位置。"
msgstr ""
"For browsers, converting superscripts to baseline characters is not always "
"desirable because superscript information is lost. To allow this distinction, "
"the Unicode Character Database contains compatibility formatting tags that "
"provide details about compatibility conversions. For ligatures, the tag is "
"``<compat>``; for superscripts, it is ``<super>``. Rich document formats such "
"as HTML use compatibility tags. For example, HTML uses custom tags to place "
"“5” in a superscript position."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:104
msgid "正规形式"
msgstr "Normalization Forms"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:105
msgid "NFD Normalization Form Canonical Decomposition 以标准等价方式来分解"
msgstr ""
"NFD Normalization Form Canonical Decomposition: decomposes by canonical "
"equivalence"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:106
msgid ""
"NFC Normalization Form Canonical Composition "
"以标准等价方式来分解，然后以标准等价重组之。若是singleton的话，重组结果有可能和分解前不同。"
msgstr ""
"NFC Normalization Form Canonical Composition: decomposes by canonical "
"equivalence, then recomposes by canonical equivalence. For a singleton, the "
"recomposition result may differ from the original before decomposition."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:107
msgid "NFKD Normalization Form Compatibility Decomposition  以兼容等价方式来分解NFKC"
msgstr ""
"NFKD Normalization Form Compatibility Decomposition: decomposes by "
"compatibility equivalence"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:108
msgid "Normalization Form Compatibility Composition 以兼容等价方式来分解，然后以标准等价重组之"
msgstr ""
"NFKC Normalization Form Compatibility Composition: decomposes by "
"compatibility equivalence, then recomposes by canonical equivalence"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:111
msgid "Tricks"
msgstr "Tricks"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:112
msgid "部分语言的长度并不是字符的长度，一个UTF-16可能是两位。"
msgstr ""
"In some languages, length does not mean character count; one UTF-16 character "
"may occupy two code units."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:113
msgid "部分语言在翻转UTF-16等多字节编码时，会处理错误。"
msgstr ""
"Some languages handle UTF-16 or other multibyte encodings incorrectly when "
"reversing strings."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:116
msgid "安全问题"
msgstr "Security Issues"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:119
msgid "Visual Spoofing"
msgstr "Visual Spoofing"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:120
msgid "例如bаidu.com(此处的a为\\u0430)和baidu.com(此处的a为\\x61)视觉上相同，但是实际上指向两个不同的域名。"
msgstr ""
"For example, bаidu.com (where a is \\u0430) and baidu.com (where a is \\x61) "
"look identical, but they actually point to two different domain names."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:122
msgid "bａidu.com(此处的a为\\uff41)和baidu.com(此处的a为\\x61)有一定的不同，但是指向两个相同的域名。"
msgstr ""
"bａidu.com (where a is \\uff41) and baidu.com (where a is \\x61) look somewhat "
"different, but they point to the same domain name."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:124
msgid "这种现象可以引起一些Spoofing或者WAF Bypass的问题。"
msgstr "This phenomenon can cause spoofing or WAF bypass issues."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:127
msgid "Best Fit"
msgstr "Best Fit"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:128
msgid "如果两个字符前后编码不同，之前的编码在之后的编码没有对应，程序会尝试找最佳字符进行自动转换。"
msgstr ""
"If two characters use different encodings and a character in the original "
"encoding has no corresponding character in the later encoding, the program "
"may try to find the best-fit character and convert it automatically."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:130
msgid "当宽字符变成了单字节字符，字符编码会有一定的变化。"
msgstr ""
"When a wide character becomes a single-byte character, the character encoding "
"changes to some extent."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:132
msgid "这种现象可能引起一些WAF Bypass。"
msgstr "This phenomenon can cause WAF bypass issues."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:135
msgid "Syntax Spoofing"
msgstr "Syntax Spoofing"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:136
msgid "以下四个Url在语法上看来是没问题的域名，但是用来做分割的字符并不是真正的分割字符，而是U+2044( ⁄ )，可以导致一些UI欺骗的问题。"
msgstr ""
"The following four URLs look syntactically like valid domain names, but the "
"characters used as separators are not real separator characters; they are "
"U+2044 ( ⁄ ), which can lead to UI spoofing issues."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:138
msgid "http://macchiato.com/x.bad.com  macchiato.com/x     bad.com"
msgstr "http://macchiato.com/x.bad.com  macchiato.com/x     bad.com"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:139
msgid "http://macchiato.com?x.bad.com  macchiato.com?x     bad.com"
msgstr "http://macchiato.com?x.bad.com  macchiato.com?x     bad.com"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:140
msgid "http://macchiato.com.x.bad.com  macchiato.com.x     bad.com"
msgstr "http://macchiato.com.x.bad.com  macchiato.com.x     bad.com"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:141
msgid "http://macchiato.com#x.bad.com  macchiato.com#x     bad.com"
msgstr "http://macchiato.com#x.bad.com  macchiato.com#x     bad.com"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:144
msgid "Punycode Spoofs"
msgstr "Punycode Spoofs"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:145
msgid "http://䕮䕵䕶䕱.com        http://xn--google.com"
msgstr "http://[U+456E U+4575 U+4576 U+4571].com        http://xn--google.com"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:146
msgid "http://䁾.com              http://xn--cnn.com"
msgstr "http://[U+407E].com              http://xn--cnn.com"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:147
msgid "http://岍岊岊岅岉岎.com    http://xn--citibank.com"
msgstr "http://[U+5C8D U+5C8A U+5C8A U+5C85 U+5C89 U+5C8E].com    http://xn--citibank.com"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:149
msgid "有些浏览器会直接显示puncode，但是也可以借助这种机制实现UI Spooof。"
msgstr ""
"Some browsers display punycode directly, but this mechanism can also be used "
"for UI spoofing."

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:152
msgid "Buffer Overflows"
msgstr "Buffer Overflows"

#: ../../source/misc/unicode.rst:153
msgid "在编码转换的时候，有的字符会变成多个字符，如Fluß → FLUSS → fluss这样可能导致BOF。"
msgstr ""
"During encoding conversion, some characters can become multiple characters, "
"such as Fluß → FLUSS → fluss, which may cause BOF."

